                            <h3>A 40-yr-old infected by elephantiasis 10 years ago gets to walk again.</h3>
                            <p>A 40-year-old man who had developed elephantiasis in his leg a decade ago and could not walk since then has got a new lease of life. After successful surgeries at <b>Max Hospital, Patparganj</b> can now walk. After a road accident 10 years ago, the patient underwent an operation on the left groin. Which resulted in disruption of the lymph nodes (lymphatics), and he developed lymphedema or elephantiasis because of accumulation of excessive fluids. He visited several hospitals across Delhi-NCR but was told that the doctors there could do nothing to cure his debilitating condition.</p>
